The Justice, Crime Prevention and Security Cluster Ministers are holding a media briefing on the recent incidents of violence in different parts of the country. Editor's note: Livestream courtesy DStv 403, you can also watch it on DStv Now. CAPE TOWN - The Justice, Crime Prevention and Security Cluster Ministers are holding a media briefing on the recent incidents of violence in different parts of the country. The cluster is expected to outline the plans government is implementing to restore law and order in the country. Around 12 people have been killed in recent violence and dozens of shops destroyed.